sentence: Looking at options trading activity among components of the S&P 500 index, there is noteworthy activity today in Walgreens Boots Alliance Inc (Symbol: WBA), where a total volume of 132,513 contracts has been traded thus far today, a contract volume which is representative of approximately 13.3 million underlying shares (given that every 1 contract represents 100 underlying shares).
That number works out to 153.6% of WBA's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 8.6 million shares.
Especially high volume was seen for the $80 strike call option expiring April 20, 2018 , with 25,009 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 2.5 million underlying shares of WBA.

Netflix Inc. (Symbol: NFLX) options are showing a volume of 132,644 contracts thus far today.
That number of contracts represents approximately 13.3 million underlying shares, working out to a sizeable 135% of NFLX's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 9.8 million shares.

Particularly high volume was seen for the $200 strike call option expiring October 27, 2017 , with 18,401 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 1.8 million underlying shares of NFLX.

Below is a chart showing NFLX's trailing twelve month trading history, with the $200 strike highlighted in orange:

And Salesforce.com Inc (Symbol: CRM) saw options trading volume of 19,702 contracts, representing approximately 2.0 million underlying shares or approximately 60.7% of CRM's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 3.2 million shares.
Especially high volume was seen for the $95 strike put option expiring June 15, 2018 , with 1,524 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 152,400 underlying shares of CRM.
